data.text:
"Kids in America" is a New Wave song by British singer Kim Wilde, released in the United Kingdom as her debut single in January 1981, and in the US in 1982.

The band No Secrets covered the song for the Jimmy Neutron, Boy Genius soundtrack in 2001. The song plays in the movie when Jimmy Neutron and the other kids of Retroville blast off into space with their modified Retroland rides to find their missing parents. PBS Kids ran a music video of the song, set to clips from the music video and PBS Kids shows.
